    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Grey Worldwide Resigns Kohler Account</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Elliott, Stuart</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Grey Worldwide resigns account of Kohler Co, plumbing products maker (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Grey Worldwide in New York, part of the Grey Global Group, has resigned the account of the Kohler Company in Kohler, Wis., the plumbing products maker. Billings were estimated at $5 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Grey Worldwide in New York, part of the Grey Global Group, has resigned the account of the Kohler Company in Kohler, Wis., the plumbing products maker. Billings were estimated at $5 million.</p>
        <p>Grey has produced print campaigns for Kohler since 1987, but ''growing differences with the client regarding creative philosophy and financial support have reached an impasse,'' Steve Blamer, president at Grey Worldwide New York, said in a memo. Executives at Kohler did not return telephone calls seeking comment.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
